Net decision: although both discs have positives (both preserve dynamics and use warm mastering), candidate 1 better preserves the core balance I value — transient snap, groove‑first bass/drums, analog warmth, and a vocal presentation that breathes and stays part of the arrangement rather than being a headline feature. Candidate 2’s front‑of‑mix, melody‑first presentation conflicts with a central dislike of vocal‑showmanship, so I reject it.

